# Security And Delivery Restrictions

## Purpose

Define non-negotiable restrictions for architecture, security review, testing
strategy, and repository hygiene.

## API Evolution Restrictions

- Do not create new SOAP endpoints.
- SOAP is legacy functionality and is expected to be deprecated; new API work must
  target REST or other approved non-SOAP interfaces.

## Mandatory Security Review Areas

For every change, explicitly assess and document impact on:

- SQL Injection (SQLi)
- Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- AI Prompt Injection
- Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)

## Security Reference Standard

- Use OWASP guidance as the default reference for security risks, mitigations, and
  review checklists.

## Testing Restrictions

- Do not limit test creation to positive scenarios only.
- Always ask for negative/failure scenarios and include them by default.
- Only skip negative scenarios when the developer explicitly confirms that is
  acceptable for the specific task.

## Repository Hygiene Restrictions

- Do not allow image files larger than 100 KB to be committed to git.
- Add and maintain a pre-commit check that blocks oversized image files.

## Implementation Note

Until the pre-commit hook is in place, treat this as a manual release blocker in
code review.
